TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            The autocomplete is a normal text input enhanced by a panel of suggested options.
            </summary>
            <typeparam name="TItem">Type of element type.</typeparam>

BoundAttributes.Name: TItem
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Specifies the type of the type parameter TItem for the MatBlazor.BaseMatAutocompleteList<TItem> component.

BoundAttributes.Name: NumberOfElementsInPopup
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Maximum number of elements displayed in the popup
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Label
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The label of the TextField
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Icon
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The Icon displayed as the leading icon for the TextField
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: StringValue
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The StringValue displayed in the TextField
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Value
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The value to be used to pre-select an item from the list
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ValueChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            ValueChanged is fired when the value is selected(by clicking on an element in the popup)
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ItemTemplate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            ItemTemplate is used to render the elements in the popup if no template is given then the string value of the objects is displayed..
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CustomStringSelector
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            This function is used to select the string part from the item, used both for filtering and displaying if no ItemTemplate is defined.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Items
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The collection which should be rendered and filtered
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Outlined
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If this parameter is true then the style of the textbox is outlined see `MatTextfield`
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnOpenedChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            OnOpenedChanged is fired when the popup dialog is opened or close and the parameter indicates whenever is it open, the default value is false
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnTextChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            OnTextChanged is fired when the string value is changed(when an input occurs in the textfield or when an item is selected)
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShowClearButton
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            This value indicates if the clear button(using a trailing icon) should be displayed, which can clear the entire text and the selected value), the default value is false
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FullWidth
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            This value indicates if the textfield and the dialog will be or not displayed in the full screen, the default value is false
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Attributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a collection of additional attributes that will be applied to the created element.
            </summary>

            Specifies one or more classnames for an DOM element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:

            Specifies an inline style for an DOM element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation: Specifies the parameter name for all child content expressions.

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Leading
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             Displays the snackbar on the "leading edge" of the screen (the left side in LTR, or the right side in RTL). 
            
             By default, snackbars are centered horizontally within the viewport. On larger screens, they can optionally be displayed on the leading edge by setting this property.
             </summary>

            To leave the snackbar open indefinitely set the timeout to -1
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: GetChildNodesCallback

<summary>
            A function that gets all the child nodes for a given parentNode.
            If lazy loading is supported and the child nodes have not yet been 
            loaded then it should return null.
            (Required)

            This function maybe called many times for a given node.
            
            Loading on Demand
            If Lazy loading is supported and the child nodes have not been loaded
            then it should return null. 
            If null is returned then <see cref="P:MatBlazor.MatTreeView`1.LoadChildNodesCallback" /> will be called to 
            get the child nodes, to it must have been set.
            </remarks>
            <example><![CDATA[
            <MatTreeView TNode="MyTreeNode"
                        GetChildNodesCallback="@GetChildNodes" />
            ...
            @code {
                private IEnumerable<MyTreeNode> GetChildNodes(MyTreeNode parentNode)
                {
                    if (parentNode.AreChildrenLoaded == false)
                        return null; // LoadChildrenCallbackAsync will be called to load the child nodes
                        
                    return parentNode.Nodes;
                }
            }        
            ]]></example>

BoundAttributes.Name: LoadChildNodesCallback
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A function to lazy load child nodes. Only required if lazy loading / load on demand
            is used. 
            (Optional - unless <see cref="P:MatBlazor.MatTreeView`1.GetChildNodesCallback" /> returns null)
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            This function is called when <see cref="P:MatBlazor.MatTreeView`1.GetChildNodesCallback" /> returns null. 
            This causes this function to be called which should load all the child nodes.
            The callback is asynchronous and should return when the values have been loaded.
            
            If an error occurs during the loading, then throw an exception (the exceptions message
            will be shown in the UI). The function many be called again for the same node in order
            to re-try.
            </remarks>
            <example><![CDATA[
            <MatTreeView TNode="MyTreeNode"
                        GetChildNodesCallback="@GetChildNodes" 
                        LoadChildNodesCallback="@LoadChildNodesAsync" />
            ...
            @code {
                private IEnumerable<MyTreeNode> GetChildNodes(MyTreeNode parentNode)
                {
                    if (parentNode.AreChildrenLoaded == false)
                        return null; // LoadChildrenCallbackAsync will be called to load the child nodes
                        
                    return parentNode.Nodes;
                }
                
                private Task<IEnumerable<MyTreeNode>> LoadChildNodesAsync(MyTreeNode parentNode)
                {
                    if (parentNode.AreChildrenLoaded == false)
                    {
                        await parentNode.Nodes = MyWebApi.GetChildNodes(parentNode.ID);
                    }
                        
                    return parentNode.Nodes;
                }        
            }        
            ]]></example>

                }

<summary>
            The VirtualScroll for Blazor displays large lists of elements performantly by only rendering the items that fit on-screen.
            Loading hundreds of elements can be slow in any browser; virtual scrolling enables a performant way to simulate all items being rendered by making the height of the container element the same as the height of total number of elements to be rendered, and then only rendering the items in view.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a value that determines how many additional items will be rendered
            before and after the visible region. This help to reduce the frequency of rendering
            during scrolling. However, higher values mean that more elements will be present
            in the page.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SpacerElement
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             Gets or sets the tag name of the HTML element that will be used as the virtualization spacer.
             One such element will be rendered before the visible items, and one more after them, using
             an explicit "height" style to control the scroll range.
            
             The default value is "div". If you are placing the <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Web.Virtualization.Virtualize`1" /> instance inside
             an element that requires a specific child tag name, consider setting that here. For example when
             rendering inside a "tbody", consider setting <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Web.Virtualization.Virtualize`1.SpacerElement" /> to the value "tr".
             </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Context
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Specifies the parameter name for all child content expressions.

TagHelpers.Name: Attributes
TagHelpers.Documentation: Merges a collection of attributes into the current element or component.

BoundAttributes.Name: @attributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Merges a collection of attributes into the current element or component.

TagHelpers.Name: Bind
TagHelpers.Documentation: Binds the provided expression to an attribute and a change event, based on the naming of the bind attribute. For example: @bind-value="..." and @bind-value:event="onchange" will assign the current value of the expression to the 'value' attribute, and assign a delegate that attempts to set the value to the 'onchange' attribute.

BoundAttributes.Name: @bind-...
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Binds the provided expression to an attribute and a change event, based on the naming of the bind attribute. For example: @bind-value="..." and @bind-value:event="onchange" will assign the current value of the expression to the 'value' attribute, and assign a delegate that attempts to set the value to the 'onchange' attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: format
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies a format to convert the value specified by the corresponding bind attribute. For example: @bind-value:format="..." will apply a format string to the value specified in @bind-value="...". The format string can currently only be used with expressions of type DateTime.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: event
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the event handler name to attach for change notifications for the value provided by the '@bind-...' attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: culture
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the culture to use for conversions.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: get
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the expression to use for binding the value to the attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: set
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the expression to use for updating the bound value when a new value is available.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: after
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies an action to run after the new value has been set.
